commText: Philip Salt and Narine are at the crease. Philip Salt is on strike. Khaleel Ahmed will open the attack

Khaleel Ahmed to Philip Salt, byes, FOUR, that's some start from Khaleel - back of a length and shaping across the right-hander, Salt saw the width and went with hard hands on the cut, gets a big edge and Pant can only palm it over to the ropes, the umpire didn't spot that though, given as byes. Not sure if anyone realized that it was bat, will go down as a half-chance
Khaleel Ahmed to Philip Salt, wide, Khaleel shortens the length and shapes one well wide of the tramlines, called as a wide
Khaleel Ahmed to Philip Salt, no run, much better from Khaleel - short of a good length and at the stumps, Salt gets behind the line and defends it to mid-off
Khaleel Ahmed to Philip Salt, no run, short of a good length and just outside off, punched off the back-foot to cover-point

Khaleel Ahmed to Philip Salt, 2 wides, Khaleel is struggling to handle the new ball, pushes one short and miles wide of off, Pant dives across in front of first slip and gets a hand onto it, kept them down to an extra wide
Khaleel Ahmed to Narine, no run, fuller length delivery and well wide of off, just inside the tramlines as Narine let it go
Khaleel Ahmed to Narine, no run, much better from Khaleel, fuller length delivery and swinging away late, Narine clears his front leg on the drive and is beaten by the swing
Khaleel Ahmed to Narine, no run, back of a length and at the stumps, Narine backs away and mistimes the pull to mid-wicket
Ishant Sharma, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack

Ishant to Philip Salt, leg byes, 1 run, short of a good length and jagging back into the right-hander, pings Salt on his glove and rolls to the off-side, must-ve come off the thigh-pad, given as a leg-bye
Ishant to Narine, no run, on a good length and holding its line outside off - Narine backs away on the swing and misses
Ishant to Narine, no run, back of a length and just outside off - Narine clears his left leg and swings hard, meets thin air as the ball flies through to Pant
Ishant to Narine, 1 run, Ishant goes full and at the stumps, turns out to be a low full-toss - Narine backs away and squeezes it to third man for a single

Ishant to Philip Salt, FOUR, nicely played, on a good length and just outside off - Salt drives it on the rise and gets enough to clear the infield, bounces over cover-point and runs away to the ropes

Ishant to Philip Salt, FOUR, back-to-back boundaries for Salt - short of a good length and just outside off, he went with hard hands on the cut and gets a thick edge on the slice, behind square on the off-side, third man is inside the ring and has no chance

Khaleel Ahmed to Narine, 2 runs, another mistimed heave, but Narine gets away with a couple - excellent effort from Stubbs, chased from mid-on, dived and pushed the ball back into play, saving a couple of runs - back of a length and at the stumps, Narine backed away on the pull and got a top-edge, high and back over the bowler's head
Khaleel Ahmed to Narine, FOUR, clattered, width on offer and Narine doesn't miss out, gets on top of the bounce and crashes the drive square over cover-point, races away to the ropes
Khaleel Ahmed to Narine, 1 run, fuller length delivery on off, Narine went hard on the drive and gets it to bounce over the bowler's leap, to the left of mid-off for a single
Khaleel Ahmed to Philip Salt, FOUR, smashed, fuller length delivery and well wide of off - lets Salt free his arms as he drills the drive over cover, runs away to the ropes
Khaleel Ahmed to Philip Salt, no run, Khaleel shortens the length and angles one across the right-hander, Salt swipes across the line and misses

Khaleel Ahmed to Philip Salt, FOUR, 15 off the over, pitched up by Khaleel, but there's width on offer and it's laced through cover, played off the back-foot and found the gap to perrfection - KKR off to a storming start once again
Ishant to Narine, SIX, drilled, on a good length and well wide of off - Narine leans forward and then launches the drive over mid-off, went sailing over the ropes for a maximum

Ishant to Narine, SIX, back-to-back sixes for Narine - he's on fire once again, short and at the stumps, Ishant doesn't have the pace to trouble the left-hander, Narine backs away and then hammers the pull over square leg
Ishant to Narine, FOUR, .. and he finds the gap once again, low full-toss from Ishant - Narine backed away and threw his hands on the drive, sliced off the thick edge and into the gap behind point

Ishant to Narine, no run, short of a good length and angling into the left-hander, a wild hack from Narine and he meets thin air. Pant makes a late call to review, but the time had run out by then. Will have to see the replays for any tiny edge

Ishant to Narine, SIX, .. and Narine continues to have some fun - Ishant can't bowl this line with all the fielders inside the ring on the off-side - lets Narine free his arms and he then carves the drive, high and over wide mid-off for another maximum

Ishant to Narine, FOUR, 26 off the over, sublime and ridiculous at the same time from Narine - on a good length and just outside off, he swings hard, gets a thick edge and sends it flying over backward point for a boundary
Time for Nortje, can he restore parity for DC?
Anrich Nortje, right-arm fast, comes into the attack
Nortje to Philip Salt, no run, short of a good length and on off, Salt is cramped for room as he pushes it to the off-side

Nortje to Philip Salt, 2 runs, chance and Warner has put it down. A costly miss for DC - back of a length and angling into the right-hander, Salt was cramped up for room, but went through with the pull, miscued it high and towards deep mid-wicket. Warner ran in, got to the ball at a good height, went reverse cupped and shelled it
Nortje to Philip Salt, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Nortje to Philip Salt, out Caught by Tristan Stubbs!! Warner can heave a sigh of relief, that missed chance hasn't cost a lot - pitched up by Nortje and Salt is once again cramped up for space, was looking to play the lofted drive, the bat turned on impact and skewed high towards mid-off - Stubbs backpedalled, kept watching the ball and reverse cupped it with ease, even as he fell on his back. Philip Salt c Tristan Stubbs b Nortje 18(12) [4s-4]
Angkrish Raghuvanshi, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Nortje to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, FOUR, Raghuvanshi starts his IPL career with a boundary - short and down leg, he swivels across and helps it over short fine with the pull, one bounce and over the ropes

Nortje to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, FOUR, sublime, back of a length and just outside off - Raghuvanshi stands tall and then punches it square past point, beat the fielder in the ring and ran away to the ropes

Nortje to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, 2 runs, short of a good length and just outside off, Raghuvanshi lets the ball come, plays with an open face and then dabs it backward of square on the off-side, comes back for the second
Rasikh Dar Salam, right-arm medium, comes into the attack
Rasikh Salam to Narine, no run, fuller length delivery from round the wicket - Narine throws his hands on the drive and missed
Rasikh Salam to Narine, FOUR, crunched, short of a good length and well wide of off, Narine gets on top of the bounce and then cuts it square past point for a boundary
Rasikh Salam to Narine, SIX, massive, back of a length and at the stumps - Narine backs away and then swivels across on the thumping pull, went high and deep into the stands at wide long-on
Back to over the wicket
Rasikh Salam to Narine, no run, slower ball pushed across the left-hander - Narine is early into the drive and toe-ends it to cover-point
Rasikh Salam to Narine, FOUR, creamed, fuller length delivery outside off - Narine stays leg-sided and then drills the drive through extra-cover, races away to the ropes

Rasikh Salam to Narine, FOUR, a 21-ball fifty for Narine, on a good length and angling across the left-hander - Narine backs away, opens the face of the bat and then uses Rasikh's pace to flay it over backward point - 88 for 1 in the batting PP, they've outdone their effort against RCB
Highest powerplay scores for KKR in the IPL 105/0 vs RCB, Bengaluru, 2017 88/1 vs DC, Vizag, today* 85/0 vs RCB, Bengaluru, 2024 76/1 vs PBKS, Kolkata, 2017 73/0 vs GL, Rajkot, 2017

Highlights (overs 1-6) -- Pant drops (tough chance) Salt 1st ball of the game -- Not a single run off the bat for the first 9 deliveries  -- Khaleel concedes 15 runs off his 2nd over -- 6 6 4 0 6 4 - Narine goes berserk against Ishant Sharma -- Warner drops Salt on 16, Nortje gets him next ball -- A 21-ball fifty for Sunil Narine
Replays on that 3.4 late review by Pant - UltraEdge spotted a murmer when the ball was next to the bat, a lost opportunity for DC
Sumit Kumar, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Sumit Kumar to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, 1 run, on a good length and shaping back into the right-hander, clipped wide of mid-wicket for a single
The keeper is up to the stumps
Sumit Kumar to Narine, no run, on a good length and well wide of off, left alone and ain't wided, was well inside the tramlines
Powerplay scores for KKR this IPL 3/43 vs SRH 0/85 vs RCB 1/88 vs DC

Sumit Kumar to Narine, 1 run, an excellent effort from Nortje, but the ball bounced in front of him - was hammered hard and flat towards long-off- he ran in, dved forward and couldn't hold on. Just about carried, but harsh to call it as a drop
Powerplay scores against DC this IPL 2/60 by PBKS 2/31 by RR 2/32 by CSK 1/88 by KKR*
Sumit Kumar to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, 1 run, fuller length delivery on the pads, whipped through mid-wicket for a single
Sumit Kumar to Narine, 1 run, short of a good length and well wide of off, slapped to deep cover for a single
Sumit Kumar to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, 1 run, on a good length and just outside off, driven to the left of long-off for a single
Axar Patel, Left arm orthodox, comes into the attack

Axar to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, FOUR, top-edge and four, nothing's going DC's way here - Raghuvanshi was shaping for the reverse sweep and was undone by Axar's extra bounce, gets a big top-edge and has enough to clear Khallel, running back at short third man
Stat: This is also the highest PP score against DC in IPL. This is also the highest PP score this IPL
Axar to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, 1 run, flighted delivery on middle and leg, worked in front of square on the on-side for a single
Axar to Narine, SIX, thumped, it's Narine's night here in Vizag, flighted delivery on middle and leg, he plays with the angle and then whips it over mid-wicket, went sailing over the ropes
Sunil Narine's batting in PP this IPL Inns: 3 Runs: 101 Balls: 45 one dismissal (run-out vs SRH) SR: 224.45 4s/6s: 9/9
Axar to Narine, 1 run, Axar pushes one quicker and wider of off, a wild swing and Narine gets a big edge on the carve - the ball dropping in betweem mid-off and deep cover

Axar to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, leg byes, 1 run, appeal for LBW, but think the impact was just outside off - was struck slightly high as well - pushed through with the angle, dragged Raghuvanshi forward and then beat him on the inside edge, flicked the pad and rolled past the keeper
Axar to Narine, SIX, hammered, another expensive over, 18 off it, pushed through by Axar and Narine nonchalantly deposited it over mid-wicket for another maximum
Sumit Kumar to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, 1 run, on a good length and just outside off, drilled back at the bowler who gets his boot in the way, deflects it towards mid-wicket for a single
Sumit Kumar to Narine, 1 run, slower ball outside off - Narine swings hard and toe-ends it towards cover for a single
Sumit Kumar to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, no run, Sumit shortens the length outside off, cut straight to the fielder at backward point
Sumit Kumar to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, 2 runs, short of a good length and well wide of off, chopped square on the off-side and Raghuvanshi is back for the second
Stat: Six is the most sixes Narine hit in an IPL innings

Sumit Kumar to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, SIX, that's a pick-up shovel and Raghuvanshi has deposited it into the mid-wicket stands, length ball at the stumps - he presses across, gets inside the line and then brings his wrists into play

Sumit Kumar to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, FOUR, this boy is showing he can bat as well - slower short ball outside off, he waits on it and then hacks it square behind point. Another expensive over and DC are bleeding boundaries
Time for the strategic break. DC badly needed this break, the run-rate is 14 and KKR are flying. Early days, but SRH's 277 is under serious trouble
Mitchell Marsh, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Mitchell Marsh to Narine, wide, banged in short by Marsh, but it sails over Narine's head and is called as a wide

Mitchell Marsh to Narine, FOUR, luck's running Narine's way today - change of pace from Marsh, slower ball outside off, Narine went hard on the drive, hit high on the bat and has enough to clear cover
Mitchell Marsh to Narine, 1 run, another slower ball outside off, drilled down to longh-off for a single
Mitchell Marsh to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, 1 run, slower ball at the stumps, eased down to long-on for a single
Mitchell Marsh to Narine, 1 run, short of a good length and on off, another slower ball and Narine mistimes the pull past the bowler
Mitchell Marsh to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, 1 run, on a length and at the pads, flicked through mid-wicket for a single
Mitchell Marsh to Narine, no run, banged in short and just outside off, Narine lets it go - it's good on height and it's not wided

Highest scores after first 10 overs in IPL 148/2 - SRH vs MI, Hyderabad, 2024 141/2 - MI vs SRH, Hyderabad, 2024 135/1 - KKR vs DC, Vizag, today* 131/3 - MI vs SRH, Abu Dhabi, 2021 131/3 - PBKS vs SRH, Hyderabad, 2014 130/0 - Deccan Chargers vs MI, Mumbai DYP, 2008
Rasikh Dar Salam [1.0-0-18-0] is back into the attack
Rasikh Salam to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, no run, on a good length and just outside off, Raghuvanshi went hard on the drive and mistimed it back at the bowler
Rasikh Salam to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, 1 run, length ball outside off, drilled to the left of cover where Marsh makes a diving half-stop, saved three runs for his team
Salam,from round the wicket
Rasikh Salam to Narine, wide, floaty delivery wide of off, but the ball pitched just outside the tramline, called as a wide
Rasikh Salam to Narine, 1 run, full-toss from Rasikh, driven to deep mid-wicket for a single

Rasikh Salam to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, SIX, that's a reverse hack and it has cleared third man - on a good length and just outside off - Raghuvanshi switches stance and then slaps it over the keeper's head, used the pace and sent it soaring
Rasikh Salam to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, no run, slightly slower and shorter of off, Raghuvanshi went with hard hands on the drive and missed

Rasikh Salam to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, SIX, beautifully played, another slower ball from Rasikh, but Raghuvanshi picked the change of pace - lets the ball come, brings his wrists into play and hoists it high and over deep mid-wicket
Anrich Nortje [1.0-0-12-1] is back into the attack
Nortje to Narine, 1 run, fuller length delivery on the leg-stump line, driven to the left of long-on for a single. This is Narine's highest IPL score
76* is highest IPL score for Narine
Nortje to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, 1 run, on a good length and at the stumps, wristily flicked through mid-wicket for a single

Nortje to Narine, SIX, he's flat-batted it over long-off and runs continue to flow - back of a length and just outside off, he backs away and forehands it over mid-off's head, this is is highest T20 score now
Nortje to Narine, 1 run, fuller length delivery at the stumps, Narine whips and gets a thick inside edge to long leg
Nortje to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, 1 run, short of a good length and just outside off, Raghuvanshi runs it down towards third man
Nortje to Narine, 2 runs, back of a length and at the stumps, Narine backs away and pulls it wide of long-on, comes back for the second
Mitchell Marsh [1.0-0-9-0] is back into the attack
Mitchell Marsh to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, 1 run, on a good length and at the stumps, nudged wide of mid-wicket for a single
Mitchell Marsh to Narine, no run, banged in short and angling across the left-hander, left alone
Mitchell Marsh to Narine, wide, Marsh tries to push one short and wide of off, but it's past the tramlines and is called as a wide
Mitchell Marsh to Narine, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Mitchell Marsh to Narine, out Caught by Pant!! That's the end of the Narine show tonight, he walks off to a big round of applause though - excellent bowling from Marsh, banged this one short, went cross-seam and made Narine swat against the line, the edge is found and Pant holds on. That'll relieve them of some serious pressure, but Narine has done a superb job once again. Narine c Pant b Mitchell Marsh 85(39) [4s-7 6s-7]
Andre Russell, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Mitchell Marsh to Russell, 1 run, fuller length delivery outside off, pushed into the gap wide of cover for a single
Mitchell Marsh to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, 1 run, a maiden IPL fifty on debut, back of a length and just outside off, dabbed behind square on the off-side for a single
Mitchell Marsh to Russell, wide, the slower bouncer from Marsh, bowled into the pitch, but went soaring over Russell's head, called as awide

Mitchell Marsh to Russell, FOUR, clubbed, that extra ball has cost Russell a boundary - low full-toss on off, he gets down low and then drags the shovel over wide mid-on, one bounce and over the ropes

Nortje to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, FOUR, a whip over mid-wicket and Rasikh can't stop it clean at deep mid-wicket. He went for a full length dive to his lefty but was in contact with the ropes whilst flicking the ball off hsi left hand
Highest 2nd wicket stand for KKR vs DC in IPL \n108 - G Gambhir, RV Uthappa, Kolkata, 2017 \n104 - SP Narine, A Raghuvanshi, Vizag, 2024*
Nortje to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, wide, back of a length angling down leg, Angkrish Raghuvanshi flicks and misses
Nortje to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Nortje to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, out Caught by Ishant at third man!! End of a terrific knock on batting debut from Angkrish Raghuvanshi. Nortje bowled it short and wide of off, Raghuvanshi thought he could ramp it for a six and opened the bat face really late. Khaleel was placed at fine third man and he didn't need to move an inch. Straight down his throat and a much-needed wicket this for DC. Angkrish Raghuvanshi c Ishant b Nortje 54(27) [4s-5 6s-3]
Shreyas Iyer, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Nortje to Shreyas Iyer, no run, short of length just outside off, Shreyas Iyer punches it to backward point
Youngest to score fifty for KKR in IPL \n18y 237d - Shubman Gill vs CSK, 2018 \n18y 303d - A Raghuvanshi vs DC, today*
Nortje to Shreyas Iyer, 1 run, I0$ bumper drifting a bit down leg, Shreyas Iyer was in control of the pull and the top-edge falls just short of the incoming fine leg fielder
Nortje to Russell, FOUR, seam length length delivery just outside off, Russell clears his front leg and stabs it through extra cover with plenty of bottom hand power...
Nortje to Russell, no run, I0$ short of length outside off, Russell looks to slap it on the off-side and gets beaten for pace
Rasikh Dar Salam [2.0-0-33-0] is back into the attack
Rasikh Salam to Shreyas Iyer, 2 runs, short and right where Iyer likes it, he slog-pulls and gets it off the thick inside half to the left of deep mid-wicket

Highest score on debut innings for KKR in IPL 158* - B McCullum vs RCB, Bengaluru, 2008 64 - Manish Pandey vs MI,, Abu Dhabi, 2014 58*- Owais Shah vs Deccan, Mumbai DYP, 2010 54 - J Kallis v CSK, Chennai, 2011 54 - Phil Salt v SRH, Kolkata, 2024 54 - A Raghuvanshi vs DC, Vizag, today*

Rasikh Salam to Shreyas Iyer, no run, Rasikh Salam asks if Rishabh heard something to which the skipper responds with a no. They decide against the review. I0$ good length just outside off, Shreyas Iyer looks for late cut and seemed to have missed the outside edge by a very close margin...
Rasikh Salam to Shreyas Iyer, 1 run, I0$ low full toss on the stumps, Shreyas Iyer flicks off the thick inside half to the right of deep square
Rasikh Salam to Russell, SIX, a juicy full toss and Andre Russell says thank you. Smashed away for an 82-metre maximum over wide long-on. Too easy...
Rasikh Salam to Russell, FOUR, Rasikh Salam goes full and wide of off, Russell goes down on his back knee and slams the cut square on the off-side. Raced away in a hurry...
Rasikh Salam to Russell, 1 run, shortens the length and takes the pace of outside off, Russell slogs and drags it off the thick inside half to the right of mid-on

Highlights (overs 7-15) -- Sumit Kumar bowls a quiet 1st over after the powerplay -- 19 runs off Axar Patel's first over -- Narine claims his highest score in T20 cricket -- A fifty on IPL batting debut for Raghuvanshi -- Sunil Narine is finally dismissed for a 39-ball 85 -- Angrish Raghvanshi holes out to third man, OUT for a 27-ball 54
Russell is standing on off-stump....
Khaleel Ahmed [2.0-0-18-0] is back into the attack
Khaleel Ahmed to Russell, wide, I0$ full and angling across the right-hander, Russell shoulders arms
Khaleel Ahmed to Russell, no run, another slower ball and Russell can't connect with his slog this time around
Shreyas Iyer was out caught behind on 14.2. He did get an edge and Rasikh Salam seemed pretty sure about that. Skipper Pant wasn't convinced and hence opted against the review...
Khaleel Ahmed to Russell, SIX, over the fielder in the deep. Full and wide of off, Russell uses plenty of bottom hand power to launch the loft over sweeper cover
Khaleel Ahmed to Russell, wide, Khaleel Ahmed steams in from round the wicket and bowls a full delivery wide of off, Russell lets it pass. Well past the tramline that one...
Khaleel Ahmed to Russell, no run, I0$ relatively high full toss (below the waits though) outside off, Russell looks to slash it on the off-side and misses
Khaleel Ahmed to Russell, 1 run, full and angles in towards off, Russell jams the drive to the left of cover. Easy single...
Khaleel Ahmed to Shreyas Iyer, 1 run, I0$ short of length outside off, Iyer pulls and gets it off the thick inside half to the left of long-on
Change of bats for Russell
Khaleel Ahmed to Russell, no run, goes wide of the crease and bowls a I0$ bumper on the stumps, Russell ducks under it
Fastest 200 by a team in IPL (in overs) 14.3 - RCB vs KXIP, 2016 14.4 - SRH vs MI, 2024 15.2 - KKR vs DC, today*

Timeout! If Russell stays for the next 3 overs, it is safe to assume that SRH's record of the highest-ever IPL score could well be under severe threat here. The surface looks a belter, but DC have been poor with DRS and slightly sloppy on the field as well...
Mitchell Marsh [2.0-0-18-1] is back into the attack
Mitchell Marsh to Shreyas Iyer, 1 run, I0$ back of a length outside off, Shreyas Iyer opens the bat face and slaps it to the left of Warner at sweeper cover
Mitchell Marsh to Russell, FOUR, Mitchell Marsh bangs it short at I0$ outside off, Russell goes hard on the cut and gets a thick top-edge that goes flies down to the third man fence on the bounce...
Mitchell Marsh to Russell, wide, bumper on the stumps, Russell ducks early and the line is a bit leg-side on this one. Perhaps a bit too high as well...
Mitchell Marsh to Russell, SIX, I0$ short and wide of off stump, Russell slogs off a thick top-edge and it travels all the way for a 76-metre maximum over mid-wicket
Mitchell Marsh to Russell, 1 run, I0$ yorker length around off, Russell looks to work leg-side and gets a thick leading edge to the left of mid-off
Mitchell Marsh to Shreyas Iyer, SIX, gee, the sound! I0$ short outside off, Shreyas Iyer fetches it from there and mauls the pull for an 80-metre maximum into the mid-wicket orbit..
Mitchell Marsh to Shreyas Iyer, no run, I0$ full and just outside off, Shreyas Iyer jams the drive to mid-off and decides against the single

Khaleel Ahmed to Russell, 2 wides, Khaleel continues from round the wicket and sprays the full ball wide of off, Russell swings and misses. The plan was to take it wide, but Khaleel Ahmed overcooked that a little bit...a slight fumbles allows an extra single as well...

Khaleel Ahmed to Shreyas Iyer, SIX, full toss outside off, Shreyas Iyer opens the bat face and slices the cut flat over backward point. Hits the boundary cushions on the full and umpire Ulhas Gandhe confirms it as well...
Khaleel Ahmed to Shreyas Iyer, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Khaleel Ahmed to Shreyas Iyer, out Caught by Tristan Stubbs!! It's the short ball once again! Shreyas Iyer looked to heave it from wide of off and didn't really get hold off the pull. Flew off the toe end high into the night sky and Stubbs settles under it at mid-off. Shreyas Iyer c Tristan Stubbs b Khaleel Ahmed 18(11) [6s-2]
Rinku Singh, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Khaleel Ahmed to Rinku Singh, wide, full and wide of off, Rinku Singh lets it pass
15 is the most sixes hit in an innings at Vizag in IPL.

Khaleel Ahmed to Rinku Singh, no ball, I0$ high full toss wide of off, Rinku Singh slaps it off the splice to the right of sweeper cover. The square leg umpire had his hand up straightaway and Russell will be ready to face the freehit next ball...
Khaleel Ahmed to Russell, 2 runs, I0$ slower back of a length delivery outside off, Russell forces it to the right of sweeper cover and a slight fumble by Sumit Kumar allows an extra run
Khaleel Ahmed vs Shreyas Iyer in IPL 20 balls 25 runs two dismissals Avg 12.5 SR 125.0
Khaleel Ahmed to Russell, no run, I0$ bumper outside off, Russell looks to flay it on the off-side and gets beaten on the top-edge
Khaleel Ahmed to Russell, 1 run, I0$ fuller than the good length outside off, Russell swings hard and slices it off the outside edge to the left of Axar at third man
Khaleel Ahmed to Rinku Singh, 1 run, I0$ full outside off, Rinku Singh goes hard on the drive and toe-ends it to the left of cover

DC are 3 overs behind on the over-rate and that means an extra fielder will have to be brought inside the circle. Only 4 outside now. Khaleel Ahmed has been subbed out and Abishek Porel comes in as an impact sub....
Anrich Nortje [3.0-0-34-2] is back into the attack

Nortje to Rinku Singh, SIX, oh-ho! Watchout Sunrisers Hyderabad - your record is under threat. A full ball wide of off, Rinku Singh tays low and slices it to the shortest area of the ground. Flies over the square third man fence for a maximum....
Nortje to Rinku Singh, SIX, a one-handed six from Rinku Singh. A low full toss wide of off, Rinku Singh slaps it for a 74-metre maximum over deep extra cover. That was timed sweetly from Rinku...
Nortje to Rinku Singh, 2 runs, Rinku looks to repeat the dose, but this time he's skewed it off the inside half to the left of Axar at sweeper cover
Nortje to Rinku Singh, wide, Nortje goes full and wide of off, Rinku Singh lets it go...This is the highest team total for KKR
Highest team total for KKR in IPL
Nortje to Rinku Singh, SIX, launched! Nortje goes full and wide of off, Rinku Singh crouches and smokes it straight over wide long-on for a mighty maximum. Russell is enjoying every bit of it...
Nortje to Rinku Singh, FOUR, I0$ length outside off, Rinku Singh spanks it off the strong bottom hand and beats the fielder at extra cover to his right. It's a boundary-storm in Vizag right now....
Nortje to Rinku Singh, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Nortje to Rinku Singh, out Caught by Warner!! A low full toss once again and this time Rinku Singh fails to get the desired connection. Loses shape trying to heave into the off-side and skews it off the toe-end towards mid-on. Warner leaps up to his fullest and claims the catch with an air of calmness. Rinku Singh c Warner b Nortje 26(8) [4s-1 6s-3]
Just 14 away and Russell is on strike. Remember there will be only 4 fielders outside the circle
Venkatesh Iyer, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Ishant Sharma [2.0-0-35-0] is back into the attack
Ishant to Russell, THATS OUT!! Bowled!!

Ishant to Russell, out Bowled!! Build a statue to this man - Ishant Sharma - the supporters of SRH must be screaming right now. Mustafizur, when playing for SRH, did something similar to Russell in 2016 IPL and now Ishant Sharma repeats the dose. A toe-crushing yorker that makes Russell fall onto the floor quite awkwardly. By the time he could bring his bat down, the stumps were in an amazing state of mess. The leg peg has gone north and the middle peg goes the opposite direction. Russell b Ishant 41(19) [4s-4 6s-3]
Ramandeep Singh, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Ishant to Ramandeep Singh, 2 runs, Ramandeep Singh gets across looking to scoop and it's deflected off his helmet to the right of mid-wicket. The physio is out to check on Ramandeep Singh and we have a brief break in play...
Ishant to Ramandeep Singh, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Ishant to Ramandeep Singh, out Caught by Prithvi Shaw!! Ishant drags the length back and keeps it well wide of off, Ramandeep Singh chases and looks to smash it over sweeper cover. Skews it off the thick inside half and Prithvi runs across to his left from cover to take a fine catch. Remember, KKR are just 2 sixes away from achieving something phenomenal here. Ramandeep Singh c Prithvi Shaw b Ishant 2(2)
Mitchell Starc, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Ishant to Starc, 1 run, I0$ full and just outside off, Starc drills it straight down the ground and Warner runs across to his left from long-off to keep it down to a single
Ishant to Venkatesh Iyer, FOUR, slower full delivery outside off, Venkatesh Iyer gets under it and thumps it back over the bowler's head for a one-bounce boundary
One six and KKR can equal the record. Can they get there? All SRH fans would be hoping and praying for is - no wide/no no-ball...

Ishant to Venkatesh Iyer, 1 run, oh no! They can't get there. A low full toss outside off and Venkatesh Iyer can only mistime the slog to the left of mid-wicket. Just a single and that is a fantastic final over from Ishant Sharma....

21:30 Local Time, 16:00 GMT, 21:30 IST: 2 hours of carnage. 2 hours of ruthless ball-striking. 2 hours of torture for the bowlers. 2 hours of relentless digging for the stat-analysts. Crikey. What have we seen in the 'I0$' A city that's generally known for its calm, clean and gentle appearance has got a brutal-bashing, not by the weather, but by the incredible boundary-sailing scenes near the stadium in PM Palem. It all started with Sunil Narine's blitzkrieg at the top, claiming his highest score in T20 cricket while at it and his Caribbean partner Russell did what he does best at the end. In the middle of this bonfire was an 18 year-old Angkrish Raghuvanshi who looked like a man hungry for an opportunity to put on a theatre of fearless batting masterclass. Raghuvanshi didn't look he was on batting debut, he looked like an IPL veteran. The nonchalance, confidence, timing and placement...And do we really need to speak about Rinku Singh, the pocket dynamite? He just arrived, launched and left no crumbs.

Angkrish Raghuvanshi - I just wanted to watch the ball and react. I had worked in the nets for the last few weeks, just had fun watching Sunil play. Having watched the SRH match, nothing's a winning score, we'll have to bowl well. Bowl in the right channels and force them into mistakes
